<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-668-322  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 668 322.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  Sept 18 1989 v23 n38 p39(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>U.S. Trust seeks speed with optical system. (Advanced GraphicApplications Inc.'s Discus 2001)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Pastore, Richard.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>United States Trust Co installed a Discus 2001 optical documentstorage and retrieval system from Advanced Graphic Applications toreplace its paper filing system.andP;  The system allows accountmanagers to access client files from optical discs and to reviewthose documents, including text, graphics and signatures.andP;  Discus2001 consists of four optical scanning stations for input and fiveIBM PC ATs and PS/2s as retrieval stations.andP;  The PCs access anoptical storage device containing 75 write-once read-manycartridges that store up to 150Gbytes of data.andP;  Banyan SystemsInc's Virtual Networking Software (VINES) connects the units.andP;  USTrust expects the system to pay for itself by 1993.andP;  Staffing fordocument management has been decreased from 17 to five employees.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Advanced Graphic Applications Inc. (products)United States Trust Co. (records and correspondence).andO;Product:   Advanced Graphic Applications DISCUS 2001 (Workstation) (usage).andO;Topic:     Optical MemoryFinancial ServicesRecords ManagementInformation Storage and Retrieval.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>